import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

# Load the data
data = pd.read_csv("data.csv")

# Melt the DataFrame
melted_data = pd.melt(data, id_vars=["Quarter"], var_name="Brand", value_name="Sales")

# Extract Year and Quarter
melted_data[['Year', 'Quarter']] = melted_data['Quarter'].str.split(' ', expand=True)

# Calculate averages
average_sales = melted_data.groupby('Brand')['Sales'].mean().reset_index()

# Set up the color palette
palette = sns.color_palette("husl", len(melted_data['Quarter'].unique()))

# Create the box plots
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
box_plot = sns.boxplot(x='Brand', y='Sales', hue='Quarter', data=melted_data, palette=palette, dodge=True)

# Overlay individual sales data points
sns.stripplot(x='Brand', y='Sales', hue='Quarter', data=melted_data, palette=palette, dodge=True, marker='o', alpha=0.5)

# Overlay the average sales line
for i, brand in enumerate(average_sales['Brand']):
    plt.plot([i - 0.2, i + 0.2], [average_sales.loc[i, 'Sales']] * 2, color='black', linestyle='--', marker='o')

# Add legend
plt.legend(title='Quarter', bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc='upper left')

# Titles and labels
plt.title('Sales Distribution and Average Sales for Mobile Phone Brands')
plt.xlabel('Brand')
plt.ylabel('Sales')
plt.xticks(rotation=45)

# Save the plot
plt.tight_layout()
plt.savefig("novice.png")
```
